            <p class="footer-note" style="margin-top:0">Distribution, expense-coverage, principal-repair, and interest ledgers are cumulative for the projection. Gross market value includes compounded NAV/price return, eligible external contributions, and reinvested A/C distributions, but excludes spendable B/D cash. New buying is paused whenever beginning-of-period margin equity is at or below the 70% resume threshold; paused contributions are held outside this projection and are not assumed to pay margin debt. Spendable B/D cash pays inflation-adjusted household expenses first; any shortfall is reported as uncovered rather than deducted from market value. Expense crossover compares each month’s B/D distributions with that month’s inflated expense target, independently of cash carried from prior months. Weekly repair is converted to a smooth monthly principal-only planning assumption and stops at zero debt. Interest is estimated on beginning monthly debt, is not capitalized or paid, and is not deducted from gross market value or spendable cash. Real brokerage timing may differ.</p>
